Date: Sat, 12 Jul 2014 18:05:50 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 763/974] MIPS: Select USB_ARCH_HAS_XHCI for CAVIUM_OCTEON_SOC

This allows us to select the xhci driver with PCI disabled.  A
supported configuration on OCTEON.

Signed-off-by: David Daney <david.daney@cavium.com>
[Original patch taken from Cavium SDK 3.1.2-568]
Signed-off-by: Quanyang Wang <quanyang.wang@windriver.com>
---
 arch/mips/Kconfig | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/mips/Kconfig b/arch/mips/Kconfig
index 3d3662f..eaa7907 100644
--- a/arch/mips/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/mips/Kconfig
@@ -771,6 +771,7 @@ config CAVIUM_OCTEON_SOC
 	select SYS_SUPPORTS_NUMA
 	select SPARSE_IRQ if NUMA
 	select HANDLE_DOMAIN_IRQ
+	select USB_ARCH_HAS_XHCI
 	help
 	  This option supports all of the Octeon SoCs and reference
 	  boards from Cavium, Inc. The Cavium Octeon processor is a
